{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"API request always carries the full allowed taxonomy label list.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is taxonomy->request-construction->API-client handoff, not just one pure function. A unit test of a helper could miss wiring bugs where the sent payload drops labels. No real OS/network/subprocess is required (stub client capture is enough), and correctness does not depend on model output, so System/Agentic are rejected.","test_description":"Wire classifier module with a stub provider client that records outbound payload. Invoke classify(document, taxonomy) and assert the outbound request includes every taxonomy label exactly once in the expected field.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Invalid provider label is mapped to \"unknown\".","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This behavior is local normalization/validation logic: given provider label + taxonomy, return sanitized label. No required module interaction, no real infra, no model-quality dependency. Higher levels are unnecessary for this specific failure mode.","test_description":"Call normalization/decision function with taxonomy [legal, technical, financial, other] and raw label \"medical\"; assert output is \"unknown\".","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.72,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Normalization is deterministic for identical raw responses.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Behavior targets determinism/idempotence of a pure normalization step. No cross-module handoff is required to expose this failure, and no infra or AI output quality is involved.","test_description":"Run normalization twice (or property-style many times) on the same raw API payload fixture and taxonomy; assert identical final label each run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Repeated live calls for same input stay consistent unless provider response changes.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly depends on live provider behavior and possible model non-determinism across calls. A mock/stub would hide exactly this failure class. Workflow is rejected because this is repeated single-step classification calls, not a multi-stage agent pipeline.","test_description":"Against the real classification API, submit identical document+taxonomy N times under controlled settings, log raw provider responses and final labels, and assert label changes only when raw provider response content changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Token budget is enforced before dispatch (truncate/reject policy).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at handoff between tokenizer/budget policy and dispatch gate: request should be blocked or transformed before client send. Unit may miss wiring where policy result is ignored. Real infra is not required (stub dispatch), and no real model output dependency exists, so System/Agentic are rejected.","test_description":"Configure small token budget, pass oversized document, use stub provider client. Assert policy outcome (truncate or reject) and verify no over-budget payload is dispatched.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Provider-reported usage for typical document stays within configured per-call budget.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This requires real AI provider token accounting; mocked usage would trivially pass and can hide true provider/model-side tokenization behavior. Integration is disqualified because correctness depends on real AI API return values (usage metadata) from live calls.","test_description":"Run representative document(s) through real provider via module, capture provider-reported token usage, and assert usage <= configured budget for each call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"On rate-limit signal, module waits and retries instead of failing fast.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary failure is retry orchestration across rate-limit handler, wait/backoff component, and provider client. Stubbed 429/RateLimit responses with fake clock can catch real logic failures. Real network is not required for minimum detection, and no model-output-quality dependence exists.","test_description":"Use stub provider that returns rate-limit error first then success. Run classify and assert module performs delay/backoff and returns successful label rather than surfacing the first error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
